gobblin.runtime.job_catalog

Class MutableJobCatalogBase

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.google.common.util.concurrent.AbstractIdleService
      • gobblin.runtime.job_catalog.JobCatalogBase
        • gobblin.runtime.job_catalog.MutableJobCatalogBase
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Service, Instrumentable, JobCatalog, JobCatalogListenersContainer, MutableJobCatalog
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    InMemoryJobCatalog

    public abstract class MutableJobCatalogBase
extends JobCatalogBase
implements MutableJobCatalog
    A base for MutableJobCatalogs. Handles notifications to listeners on calls to put(gobblin.runtime.api.JobSpec), remove(java.net.URI), as well as the state of the Service.

      • doPut

        protected abstract JobSpec doPut(JobSpec jobSpec)
        Add the JobSpec to the catalog. If a JobSpec already existed with that URI, it should be replaced and the old one returned.
        Returns:
        if a JobSpec already existed with that URI, return the old JobSpec. Otherwise return null.
